
[1]desperate

   DESPERATE, a. [L. To despair.]

   1. Without hope.

   I am desperate of obtaining her.

   2. Without care of safety; rash; fearless of danger; as a desperate
   man. Hence,

   3. Furious, as a man in despair.

   4. Hopeless; despaired of; lost beyond hope of recovery; irretrievable;
   irrecoverable; forlorn. We speak of a desperate case of disease,
   desperate fortunes, a desperate situation or condition.

   5. In a popular sense, great in the extreme; as a desperate sot or
   fool.
